<doc f='include/c++/11/sstream' l='812'>/**
       *  @brief  Starts with an existing string buffer.
       *  @param  __str  A string to copy as a starting buffer.
       *  @param  __mode  Whether the buffer can read, or write, or both.
       *
       *  @c ios_base::out is automatically included in @a mode.
       *
       *  Initializes @c sb using @a str and @c mode|out, and passes @c &amp;sb
       *  to the base class initializer.
       *
       *  That&apos;s a lie.  We initialize the base class with NULL, because the
       *  string class does its own memory management.
      */</doc>
